Subquery - query inside Nother Query. Breaks complex query into smaller, manageble pieces.

Types:
- Non-Correlated - can run independently from main query
- Correlated - relies on values from the main query

By result type:
- Scalar subquery - returns a singgle value
- Row subquery - returns multiple rows & single column
- Table sunquery - returns multiple rows & miltiple columns

By location:
- Subruery in SELECT
- Subruery in FROM
- Subruery in JOIN 
- Subruery in WHERE 
  - ANY - checks if value matches ANY value within the list
  - ALL - checks if value matches ALL values within the list
  - EXISTS (NON EXISTS) - check if subquery returns any rows

USE CASES:
- Create temporary result set
- Prepare data before joining tables
- Dynamic & Complex filtering
- Check the existence of rows from another tables
- Row by Row comparison (correlated subquery)
